main event: A UFO report from Dahlgren, Va., Mathewson Field, on 3 Jan 1953 at 2215Z involved the sighting of a single object for approximately 1 minute.
interesting points: The object was observed to travel in a straight line and resembled a 'shooting star'.
There was no trail or sound associated with the object.
The object disappeared within 62 to 1 seconds of observation.
No physical evidence or photographs were obtained.
Another sighting of a fireball moving from NE to SW at 2052 pm was reported near Upper Darby, PA, as well as a bright meteor observation on 23 Jan 1953 at 22:30 EST.
